    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Yes you can use options.transformData.item like this:\n\n``` js\nvar hits = instantsearch.widgets.hits({\n  transformData: {\n    item: function(hit) {\n      // change hit then\n      // hit.show = true/false\n      // return hit\n    }\n  }\n});\n```\n\nThen in your template, just conditionally display the hit based on `show` value: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/6027525/how-do-i-accomplish-an-if-else-in-mustache-js\n",
    "created_at": "2016-04-13T15:36:15Z",
